  "description": "A thickened portion of an underground stem that stores energy for the plant. Each \"eye\" (growth bud) on a tuber can produce a new shoot. In gardening, tubers are planted directly in the ground at the appropriate depth and spacing. The most common garden tuber is the potato.",
